# Planning and design docs

## Single source of truth

All architecture, phases, and implementation design live in committed repo files:

- **Primary plan:** [`docs/PLAN.md`](docs/PLAN.md)

Edit `docs/PLAN.md` directly. Do not create parallel plan files (e.g.
`PLAN-implementation.md`, `PLAN-draft.md`) unless the user explicitly asks for
a temporary split.

## Do not use Cursor internal plans

Do **not** treat Cursor's internal plan feature as the project plan:

- No authoring or updating `~/.cursor/plans/*.plan.md` as the canonical design
- No copying plans to/from Cursor-only paths instead of the repo
- No "save to repo later" -- changes belong in `docs/PLAN.md` in the same turn

Internal plans are untracked, invisible in git, and easy to lose. They caused
confusion when they diverged from `docs/PLAN.md`.

## When design changes

1. Update [`docs/PLAN.md`](docs/PLAN.md) in this repository
2. Commit plan changes when the user asks (or as part of an agreed docs pass)
3. Reference `docs/PLAN.md` in code, rules, and PRs -- not Cursor plan URLs

## Agent behavior

- Read design from `docs/PLAN.md`, not from conversation-only or Cursor-internal state
- If the user iterates on design, edit `docs/PLAN.md` (plan iteration), not a shadow file
- If `docs/PLAN.md` and chat history disagree, the committed file wins unless the user is actively revising it
